# Git — no commit or push without explicit request

## Required behavior

- **Never** run `git commit`, `git push`, `git add` (for the purpose of committing), or create/amend commits unless the user **explicitly** asks in the current message (e.g. "commit", "push", "napravi commit", "pushuj na git").
- **Never** push to remote (including `git push`, `gh`, force push) unless explicitly requested.
- Deploying (e.g. Vercel) is allowed when asked for deployment/preview — that is not the same as git push, but still do not commit local changes unless asked.

## When the user asks to commit

Follow the full git safety workflow: status, diff, log, draft message, commit, verify. Do not push unless they also ask to push.

## If unsure

Ask: "Da li želiš da napravim commit (i/ili push)?" — do not assume.

## Examples

- User: "promeni boju u srebro" → change code only, **no** commit/push.
- User: "deployuj na vercel" → deploy only, **no** commit unless they also ask.
- User: "commituj izmene" → commit; push only if they say push.
